<p dir=3D"auto"><strong>News:</strong></p>
<ul dir=3D"auto">
<li>We have updated the tutorials in Jupyter Notebook to help you walk thro=
ugh RLCard! Please check <a href=3D"https://github.com/datamllab/rlcard-tut=
orial">RLCard Tutorial</a>.</li>
<li>All the algorithms can suppport <a href=3D"https://github.com/PettingZo=
o-Team/PettingZoo">PettingZoo</a> now. Please check <a href=3D"https://gith=
ub.com/datamllab/rlcard/blob/master/examples/pettingzoo">here</a>. Thanks t=
he contribtuion from <a href=3D"https://github.com/ycheng517">Yifei Cheng</=
a>.</li>
<li>Please follow <a href=3D"https://github.com/kwai/DouZero">DouZero</a>, =
a strong Dou Dizhu AI and the <a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/abs/2106.06135" =
rel=3D"nofollow">ICML 2021 paper</a>. An online demo is available <a href=
=3D"https://douzero.org/" rel=3D"nofollow">here</a>. The algorithm is also =
integrated in RLCard. See <a href=3D"https://github.com/datamllab/rlcard/bl=
ob/master/docs/toy-examples.md#training-dmc-on-dou-dizhu">Training DMC on D=
ou Dizhu</a>.</li>
<li>Our package is used in <a href=3D"https://github.com/PettingZoo-Team/Pe=
ttingZoo">PettingZoo</a>. Please check it out!</li>
<li>We have released RLCard-Showdown, GUI demo for RLCard. Please check out=
 <a href=3D"https://github.com/datamllab/rlcard-showdown">here</a>!</li>
<li>Jupyter Notebook tutorial available! We add some examples in R to call =
Python interfaces of RLCard with reticulate. See <a href=3D"https://github.=
com/datamllab/rlcard/blob/master/docs/toy-examples-r.md">here</a></li>
<li>Thanks for the contribution of <a href=3D"https://github.com/Clarit7">@=
Clarit7</a> for supporting different number of players in Blackjack. We cal=
l for contributions for gradually making the games more configurable. See <=
a href=3D"https://github.com/datamllab/rlcard/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#m=
aking-configurable-environments">here</a> for more details.</li>
<li>Thanks for the contribution of <a href=3D"https://github.com/Clarit7">@=
Clarit7</a> for the Blackjack and Limit Hold'em human interface.</li>
<li>Now RLCard supports environment local seeding and multiprocessing. Than=
ks for the testing scripts provided by <a href=3D"https://github.com/weepin=
gwillowben">@weepingwillowben</a>.</li>
<li>Human interface of NoLimit Holdem available. The action space of NoLimi=
t Holdem has been abstracted. Thanks for the contribution of <a href=3D"htt=
ps://github.com/AdrianP-">@AdrianP-</a>.</li>
<li>New game Gin Rummy and human GUI available. Thanks for the contribution=
 of <a href=3D"https://github.com/billh0420">@billh0420</a>.</li>
<li>PyTorch implementation available. Thanks for the contribution of <a hre=
f=3D"https://github.com/mjudell">@mjudell</a>.</li>
</ul>
