<p dir=3D"auto">You can use the the following interface to make an environm=
ent. You may optionally specify some configurations with a dictionary.</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto">
<li><strong>env =3D rlcard.make(env_id, config=3D{})</strong>: Make an envi=
ronment. <code>env_id</code> is a string of a environment; <code>config</co=
de> is a dictionary that specifies some environment configurations, which a=
re as follows.
<ul dir=3D"auto">
<li><code>seed</code>: Default <code>None</code>. Set a environment local r=
andom seed for reproducing the results.</li>
<li><code>allow_step_back</code>: Default <code>False</code>. <code>True</c=
ode> if allowing <code>step_back</code> function to traverse backward in th=
e tree.</li>
<li>Game specific configurations: These fields start with <code>game_</code=
>. Currently, we only support <code>game_num_players</code> in Blackjack, .=
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p dir=3D"auto">Once the environemnt is made, we can access some informatio=
n of the game.</p>
<ul dir=3D"auto">
<li><strong>env.num_actions</strong>: The number of actions.</li>
<li><strong>env.num_players</strong>: The number of players.</li>
<li><strong>env.state_shape</strong>: The shape of the state space of the o=
bservations.</li>
<li><strong>env.action_shape</strong>: The shape of the action features (Do=
u Dizhu's action can encoded as features)</li>
</ul>
